Russian Movers: Bank Saint Petersburg, Raspadskaya, Uralkali

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-06-09T09:45:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/russian-movers-bank-saint-petersburg-raspadskaya-uralkali.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  traded
little changed at 1,663.79 by 1:31 p.m. in Moscow, erasing an
earlier advance of as much as 0.8 percent. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index was unchanged at 1,911.41.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  Bank Saint Petersburg (BSPB RX) advanced for a third day,
its longest winning streak in more than a month, after the
lender posted a sixfold jump in first-quarter profit. The shares
climbed as much as 2.9 percent and last traded 2.2 percent
higher at 142.94 rubles.  OAO Raspadskaya (RASP RX) slumped after Russian billionaire
 Gennady Timchenko ’s spokesman said the businessman isn’t
interested in acquiring a stake in the Russian coal producer.
The shares fell as much as 4.6 percent erasing earlier gains,
and last traded 2.9 percent lower at 163.93 rubles.  OAO Uralkali (URKA RX),  Russia ’s largest potash producer,
rose the most this month after Interfax reported that owner
Suleiman Kerimov may buy control of a state-owned competitor in
Belarus for $15 billion. Uralkali added as much as 4.5 percent
to 252 rubles, the biggest intraday jump since May 31, before
paring the advance to 1.2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
